<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ861218-0131 </DOCNO><HL> Financing Business:Sage Software Inc.</HL><DD> 12/18/86</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> SGSIINITIAL STOCK OFFERINGS (INI)STOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK) </IN><TEXT>   SAGE SOFTWARE INC. sold 1.8 million common shares at $12.50 each in its initial offering, Alex. Brown andamp; Sons Inc. lead underwriter said. Of the total, the Rockville, Md.,-based concern sold one million shares and holders the rest. Proceeds to the company will be used for general purposes, principally working capital. The company develops, markets and supports an integrated family of computer-aided software-engineering tools for International Business Machines Corp. and compatible mainframe computers. </TEXT></DOC>